Production Uplift Program Summary:

  • Program Initiation: Mobilisation of personnel/equipment for Production Uplift Program (announced 31 Jan 2025) at Odin and Vali gas fields (PRL 211 and ATP 2021 JVs).
  • Measures: Remediation of scale, additional production intervals in Toolachee Formation (Vali), swab/re-perforation at Vali-3.
  • Timeline: Operations over 6 weeks, bulk in August, completion by early September 2025.
  • Expected Impact:
  • Production uplift: 2.1–5.6 MMscf/d raw gas (vs. current 3.2 MMscf/d).
  • Cash payback: <3 months (P50 estimate).
  • Offtake: Gas sold via long-term contracts with AGL and ENGIE’s Pelican Point Power.

(No material financial or capital structure changes disclosed.)

Summary of ASX Announcement

Announcement Type: Quarterly Performance Report

  • Performance Highlights (June 2025 Quarter)
  • Portfolio returned +12.2% (vs. ASX200AI +9.5%).
  • 5-year annualized return: 21.0% p.a. (vs. ASX200AI +11.8% p.a.).

  • Key Contributors: Strong commodity price rises (gold, copper), corporate activity (takeover proposals for long positions), and operational updates.

  • Key Stock Performers (QoQ Returns)

  • NexGen Energy (+47%): Uranium price rebound (~16% QoQ).
  • Finning International (+44%): Strong Q1 results, EPS growth outlook.

  • Santos (+15%): Takeover proposal at 28% premium (US$5.76/share).

  • Macro/Economic Observations

  • Tariff volatility: U.S. "Liberation Day" tariffs drove April sell-off, but markets recovered to all-time highs.
  • U.S. fiscal concerns: Rising treasury yields (30-year at ~5%), USD depreciation (~10% YTD).

  • Portfolio positioning: Value skew (median long P/E: 11x, 8% FCF yield).

  • Portfolio Metrics (30 June 2025)

  • Net exposure: 77% (168% long, 92% short).

  • Geographic focus: 71% Australia/NZ, 32% North America, 31% Europe.

  • Cash/NTA

  • NTA (after tax): $3.12 (vs. share price: $2.90).

Material Takeaways for Traders/Investors

  1. Outperformance vs. benchmark (+2.7% QoQ) driven by commodity-linked stocks and M&A activity.
  2. Santos takeover bid signals undervaluation in energy sector.
  3. High concentration in value stocks with attractive fundamentals (low P/E, high FCF).

No material capital-raising, trading halt, or structural changes identified.

Material Information Summary (ASX: SVY) – Exploration Update

Key Highlights

  • Significant Gold Intercepts:
  • Fairview North:
    • 59m @ 1.31g/t Au (from surface), including 27m @ 2.33g/t Au and 3m @ 10.81g/t Au.
    • 42m @ 1.57g/t Au (from 23m), including 8m @ 4.76g/t Au.

  • Fairview South (previously reported):

    • 40m @ 1.96g/t Au (from surface), including 9m @ 7.15g/t Au.

  • Metallurgical Testwork:

  • Heap Leach Potential: 80%+ gold recoveries demonstrated in column/bottle-roll tests.

  • Gravity recovery improved overall recoveries to 85–95.3%.

  • Exploration Upside:

  • Fairview North and South form part of a +10km mineralised structure.
  • Planned follow-up RC drilling at Flexure Zones A, B, and C.

Conclusion

Drilling confirms shallow, broad, heap-leachable gold mineralisation with high-grade zones. Metallurgical tests support low-cost extraction potential. Further drilling aims to expand the mineralised footprint.

No material capital/financial updates or timetable events.
